{
  "id": "EUVD-2026-39638",
  "enisaUuid": "4eac8ab0-ba54-3f20-ba31-2bbe3e28f83c",
  "description": "The WSO2 API Manager's message flow component, when processing WS-Addressing headers, does not sufficiently validate or restrict user-controlled input within these headers. This omission allows an attacker to manipulate WS-Addressing headers to specify arbitrary destinations for server-initiated requests.\n\nSuccessful exploitation allows an unauthenticated attacker to control the destination of server-initiated requests originating from the WSO2 API Manager. This direct control can enable unauthorized access to internal network resources or services that would typically be inaccessible from external networks.",
